      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of May 21 article about Mumia Abu-Jamal, convicted killer of Philadelphia police officer; he was never affiliated with National Public Radio</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article last Sunday about Mumia Abu-Jamal, the convicted killer of a Philadelphia police officer, referred incorrectly to his former affiliation as a broadcast commentator. While National Public Radio agreed in 1994 to broadcast his occasional commentaries, it reversed itself before doing so, citing ''serious misgivings about the appropriateness'' of using a convicted murderer who was seeking a new trial.</p>
      </block>
